            <tss:characteristics>
               <tss:characteristic name="articleTitle">murāsilāt: al-shām fī 23 al-jārī</tss:characteristic>
               <tss:characteristic name="publicationTitle">lisān al-ḥāl</tss:characteristic>
               <tss:characteristic name="abstractText">[achievements of the] Reform program, public works: every since the formation of a municipality the people complained about the absence of any real works being done by this administrative body. now, as corruption is dealt with, we see improvements of large roads (al-jādāt al-kabīra), such as the alleys of the Mīdān and Ṣāliḥiyya, which had been solidly paved, beautification of the citadel, its connection with a fine road for pedestrians and coaches. these two most important alleys are in a bad state: in the summer heavy clouds of dust rise into the air and during the winter they are flooded with water, so that it is easier to take small boats.<html:br/>
                  <html:br/>- in some alleyways and aswāq, lamps are ignited at night but they do not help the people to actually see anything. but <tei:measureGrp>the officials of the lamps collect from each shop or warehouse <tei:measure commodity="currency" unit="ops" quantity="5">Ps 5</tei:measure> 
                     <tei:measure commodity="tax" unit="month" quantity="1">per mensem as a tax for the majlis al-baladiyya</tei:measure>
                  </tei:measureGrp>
                  <html:br/>- it had been announced that the local municipality will closely follow the example of Beirut, both nothing had happened. as some £T 3.000 are annually collected for the repair of the city, something should be done!</tss:characteristic>
